<span id="freeTextContainer11074040384908828948">I didn&apos;t like this book, skipping over and skimming through the last half as fast as I could.<br/><br/>Set in 1135 England, it tells the story of Stephen and Maude&apos;s fight over the thone. <br/><br/>I picked out this as my first Penman novel because it was set in the era of Brother Cadfael. The amount of time spent on Maude&apos;s unhappy marriage and Stephens wife was tedious and jumping from one drama to the next drama was too much action and not enough story or character building. The history was fascinating but the w</span>
  <span id="freeText11074040384908828948" style="display:none">I didn't like this book, skipping over and skimming through the last half as fast as I could.<br /><br />Set in 1135 England, it tells the story of Stephen and Maude's fight over the thone. <br /><br />I picked out this as my first Penman novel because it was set in the era of Brother Cadfael. The amount of time spent on Maude's unhappy marriage and Stephens wife was tedious and jumping from one drama to the next drama was too much action and not enough story or character building. The history was fascinating but the writing style and chopped up story made it less than enjoyable to read. </span>
